painting-took-a-winding-path-from-hitlers-munich-apartment-to-an-american-journalists-home-to-the-national-gallery-in-london-180988733/</guid></item><item><title>这种微小的真菌在美国宇航局的灭菌协议中幸存下来，并且有可能足以污染火星</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-microscopic-fungus-survived-nasas-sterilization-protocols-and-is-hardy-enough-to-potentially-contaminate-mars-180988728/</link><description>这些微生物是从该机构的洁净室中收集的，专家们在洁净室中精心控制的环境中建造航天器。调查结果揭示了该机构在防止长期搭便车者方面的程序存在缺陷</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 18:57:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-microscopic-fungus-survived-nasas-sterilization-protocols-and-is-hardy-enough-to-potentially-contaminate-mars-180988728/</guid></item><item><title>观看 17 张复杂的显微镜照片，让微型世界变得无比巨大。他们赢得了年度最佳形象大赛</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-17-intricate-microscope-photographs-that-make-the-miniature-world-immense-they-won-the-evident-image-of-the-year-contest-180988722/</link><description>第六届年度竞赛展示了科学显微成像，照亮了自然界的微小部分，从单个细胞到节肢动物、硅藻和斑马鱼大脑</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 18:45:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-17-intricate-microscope-photographs-that-make-the-miniature-world-immense-they-won-the-evident-image-of-the-year-contest-180988722/</guid></item><item><title>这些海藻在海浪扰动时会发光。他们的生物发光可以为未来的无电灯供电</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-marine-algae-glow-when-waves-disturb-them-their-bioluminescence-could-power-electricity-free-lamps-of-the-future-180988721/</link><description>这些单细胞生物通常只会闪烁几毫秒，但研究人员找到了维持其发光的方法。这项技术有一天可以用来照亮机器人在深海或太空中的道路</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 15:43:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-marine-algae-glow-when-waves-disturb-them-their-bioluminescence-could-power-electricity-free-lamps-of-the-future-180988721/</guid></item><item><title>新数据显示，密歇根州罗亚尔岛国家公园的狼群数量激增，数量达到近 50 年来的最高水平</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/wolves-are-thriving-at-michigans-isle-royale-national-park-reaching-their-highest-numbers-in-almost-50-years-new-data-suggests-180988727/</link><description>科学家估计，目前有 37 只驼鹿在崎岖的群岛上漫步，这导致了驼鹿数量的减少。但捕食者与猎物的比例可能会趋于稳定</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/wolves-are-thriving-at-michigans-isle-royale-national-park-reaching-their-highest-numbers-in-almost-50-years-new-data-suggests-180988727/</guid></item><item><title>马铃薯不仅为安第斯山脉的古代土著社区提供食物，美味的块茎还重塑了人们的 DNA</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/potatoes-didnt-just-feed-ancient-indigenous-communities-in-the-andes-the-tasty-tubers-also-reshaped-peoples-dna-180988732/</link><description>一项新的研究发现，生活在现在秘鲁境内的安第斯土著人有一个名为 AMY1 的基因的额外副本，该基因有助于身体消化淀粉</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 21:13:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/potatoes-didnt-just-feed-ancient-indigenous-communities-in-the-andes-the-tasty-tubers-also-reshaped-peoples-dna-180988732/</guid></item><item><title>NASA 刚刚上传了 Artemis 2 任务的 12,000 多张令人惊叹的照片。这是我们最喜欢的一些</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-just-uploaded-more-than-12000-stunning-photos-from-the-artemis-2-mission-here-are-a-few-of-our-favorites-180988697/</link><description>尽管此次任务的四名宇航员在太空中向地球发送了一些照片，但大多数照片在返回地球后都需要通过物理存储卡传送</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 20:32:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-just-uploaded-more-than-12000-stunning-photos-from-the-artemis-2-mission-here-are-a-few-of-our-favorites-180988697/</guid></item><item><title>玛丽莲·梦露 (Marilyn Monroe) 为庆祝她 100 岁生日而推出的系列系列，穿越好莱坞魅力，展现这位明星人性的一面</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/marilyn-monroe-collections-assembled-for-her-100th-birthday-cut-through-hollywood-glamour-to-reveal-the-stars-human-side-180988726/</link><description>这位电影明星的精选服装、珠宝和深色私人信件将被拍卖，以庆祝她的生日</description><pubDate>Tu